**Configure Network**

Set both VMs to the **same network**.

In VirtualBox:

```
Settings → Network → Adapter
Mode: Bridge Adapter
```

![image.png](attachment:ebf1a655-99f9-4080-8ad8-a9e2739ca45b:image.png)

This allows Kali to **attack Windows**.

Check connectivity between kali and and Windows OS

On Kali:  ping windows OS and if its responding, this means they are on the same network and can talk to each other 

```
ping <windows_ip>
```

On Windows: ping Kali OS and if its responding, this means they are on the same network and can talk to each other 

```
ping <kali>
```
